.TH FMT-TABLE 1 "2026-02-19" "fmt-table" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
fmt-table \- render aligned terminal tables with persisted session state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fmt-table
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fmt-table
renders markdown-style terminal tables and can persist session state between invocations.
The title row is styled with terminal ANSI bold sequences.
It supports append workflows where newly added rows can redraw a previous table snapshot
in interactive terminals.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -t , " --title-row " TEXT
Comma-separated title row.
.TP
.BR -r , " --row " TEXT
Comma-separated content row. Repeatable.
.TP
.BR -w , " --width " STR
Width strategy:
.B dynamic
,
.B equal
,
.B full
, or integer width.
.TP
.BR -f , " --frame"
Accepted for compatibility (markdown-only output).
.TP
.BR -e , " --end"
Accepted for compatibility (markdown-only output).
.TP
.BR -a , " --append"
Append mode (compatibility behavior).
.TP
.BR -c , " --clear-state"
Clear persisted state.
.TP
.BR -n , " --new-session"
Ignore prior state on this run.
.TP
.BR -m , " --markdown"
Accepted for compatibility (markdown-only output).
.TP
.BR -b1 , " --bold-first-column"
Accepted for compatibility.
.TP
.BR -s , " --screen"
Accepted for compatibility.
.TP
.BR -F , " --force"
Accepted for compatibility.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Show help and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.cache/fmt-table/state.json
Persisted table session state.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B fmt-table -n -t "Task,Status" -r "Build,Running"
.PP
.B fmt-table -r "Test,Queued"
.PP
.B fmt-table -n -m -t "A,B" -r "1,2"
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid command usage.
